<p>The Excel function <i>QUARTILE.INC(array, quart)</i> provides the desire=
d quartile value for a given array of data, using Method 3 from above. The =
<i>QUARTILE</i> function is a legacy function from Excel 2007 or earlier, g=
iving the same output of the function <i>QUARTILE.INC</i>. In the function,=
 <i>array</i> is the dataset of numbers that is being analyzed and <i>quart=
</i> is any of the following 5 values depending on which quartile is being =
calculated. <sup id=3D"cite_ref-9" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quartile#cite_note-9"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</=
span>9<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
